      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-04T15:02:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In general I like to avoid \"git add --all\", as it\u0027s possible to check in undesired things.  Since we know the list of files we should\u0027ve changed, why not \"git add\" each file individually?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 258,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 258,
        "endChar": 45
      },
